<TITLE> 2 killed in road crashes in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 25 (bdnews24.com)--Two people were killed in separate road accidents at Jatrabari in Dhaka on Thursday night and Friday afternoon, police said. The victims were identified as Nayan Sardar, 27, son of Abdul Latif Sardar of Shaheber Haat in Barisal, and an unidentified man aged around 70. Sub-inspector of Jatrabari Police Station Saiful Islam said Utshab Paribahan, a bus headed towards Narayanganj from Dhaka, collided with Nayan's motorcycle while he was coming to Jatrabari from Dhaka with his friend Rana Kaiser. People admitted them to Dhaka Medical College Hospital but Nayan was declared dead. A severely injured Rana was receiving treatment at the hospital. Islam said the driver fled the scene leaving the bus on the spot. Angry people vandalised the bus. Police took the bus and motorcycle under custody later. In the second accident, the old man died on the spot on Dhaka-Chittagong highway, adjacent to a security check-post, when a vehicle run over him. Police suspect the man was trying to get across the road. 
